THE closure of seven hospital wards has marked the start of the winter vomiting bug season, health officials have said. Bug shuts hospital wards THE closure of seven hospital wards has marked the start of the winter vomiting bug season, health officials have said.Health Protection Scotland (HPS) confirmed that norovirus led to the closures at six hospitals in four NHS boards across Scotland.Norovirus generally causes mild gastrointestinal symptoms such as vomiting and diarrhoea but can be more serious among the elderly and people who are already unwell. 